  "texts": [
    "The probability p U la z+1 is calculated similarly.",
    "ThenU la t = U la z if p U la z > p U la z+1 and U la t = U la z+1 if p U la z ≤ p U la z+1.",
    "If U la t = U la z+1, the pointer z will move to z + 1 at timestep t + 1.",
    "Due to the scene complexity, the pointer z may not move during many navigation steps.",
    "Therefore, we force the movement of z when it continuously points to the same position (see Fig. 4 for example)."
